<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="pure-adj">pure <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /pjʊə(r)/    美 /pjʊr/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>纯的；纯粹的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>pure gold</strong> / English
纯金/纯正的英语</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>纯洁的；纯净的</strong></h4>
<p>反 impure ： </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>pure water
纯净的水</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The air is very pure, and it doesn’t snow very much.
这里的空气非常清新，而且很少下雪。</p><footer>外研⑧ – 1</footer></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>[只用于名词前，无比较级] 完全的；十足的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>by pure chance</strong>
纯属偶然</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>purely /'pjʊəli/ adv   </p>
<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>This T-shirt is made of high quality <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (纯的) cotton.  （2012 陕西）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. pure  </p></div>